explanation: The solution iterates through each bit of the input integer, shifting the result left and ORing it with the corresponding bit of the input. This effectively reverses the bit order.  The algorithm has a constant time complexity as it performs a fixed number of operations regardless of the input size. It also has a constant space complexity as it only uses a few integer variables.

